  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM2.10.9">
<l>tūvaṭiviṉ pārmakaḷpū maṅkai yōṭu cuṭarāḻi caṅkirupāl polintu tōṉṟa</l>
<l>kāvaṭiviṉ kaṟpakamē pōla niṉṟu kalantavarkaṭ karuḷpuriyuṅ karutti ṉāṉai</l>
<l>cēvaṭikai tiruvāykaṇ civanta vāṭai cempoṉcey tiruvuruva māṉāṉ ṟaṉṉai</l>
<l>tīvaṭiviṉ civaṉayaṉē pōlvār maṉṉu tirukkōva lūrataṉuḷ kaṇṭēṉ nāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The one whose object is giving grace to those close [to him],</l>
<l rend="indent">enduring like the [wish-giving] kalpaka [tree] with a forest[-like] size,</l>
<l>Where appears shining at both sides the bright discus and conch,</l>
<l rend="indent">along with the earth lady of pure beauty and the lady of the flower,</l>
<l>The one who became a divine form with the red of rose gold</l>
<l rend="indent">on rosy feet, hands, divine mouth, eyes, and reddened garment,</l>
<l>I saw in Tirukkōvalūr where dwell those like Śiva with a fiery form</l>
<l rend="indent">and the Unborn [Brahmā].</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
